Angular-

Angular is open source web framework and development platform, for building web, desktop, mobile applications.

It is built on Typescript and maintained by Google.

It is used to create single page applications (SPA) and progressive web applications (PWA).

Single Page Application (SPA) is a web application that loads a single HTML page and 

dynamically updates the content as the user interacts with the app without requiring a full page reload.

Progressive Web Application (PWA) is a web application that uses modern web technologies to provide

a native app-like experience to users, including offline capabilities, push notifications, and fast loading times.
 
Angular JS is the first version of Angular, released in 2010. It is based on JavaScript 

and uses a Model-View-Controller (MVC) architecture. 

Angular JS is no longer actively maintained, 

and it is recommended to use Angular (version 2 and above) for new projects.
 
 
ng new project-name

This command is used to create a new Angular project with the specified name.
 
ng serve

This command is used to start the development server and serve the Angular application.

It runs the application on port 4200 by default, 

and you can access it in the browser at http://localhost:4200.
 
ng build

This command is used to build the Angular application for production. 

It compiles the application and optimizes it for deployment.
 
npm start

This command is used to start the Angular application using the npm package manager.
 
